1
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:21,146
Hulk Hogan, who some consider to be

2
00:00:21,229 --> 00:00:23,690
the biggest wrestling star of all time,

3
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:24,649
has died.

4
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,777
Terry Bollea, better known as Hulk Hogan,

5
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:32,032
died today after suffering cardiac arrest
at his home in Clearwater, Florida.

6
00:00:32,115 --> 00:00:36,286
Hogan's manager tells us
that he passed away surrounded by family.

7
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:42,125
His wild personality, pumped up physique,

8
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:43,501
and handlebar mustache

9
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:46,171
made him the face
of professional wrestling.

10
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:49,340
His legacy also comes with controversy.

11
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:52,886
This won't surprise you, but I used
to watch him every day after school.

12
00:00:52,969 --> 00:00:54,471
-Like a lot of kids.
-Yeah.

13
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:56,556
Unlike a lot of superheroes,
Superman, Batman,

14
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:58,933
you couldn't touch them, he was tangible.

15
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,518
-Sure.
-To a lot of people.

16
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:03,772
They're very sad to see
their legend, their childhood hero,

17
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:06,941
gone in what seems like such a sudden way.

18
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:33,051
Oh.

19
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:36,179
That's the hardest part, standing up.

20
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:39,808
Old people take a long time to get going.

21
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:41,976
Whoo.

22
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:52,445
When I was the world's champion,
I had this crazy gym.

23
00:01:52,529 --> 00:01:58,118
Over the years, we've kind of scaled down
to the… to the Geritol equipment here.

24
00:02:03,039 --> 00:02:04,791
Do you feel strong?

25
00:02:04,874 --> 00:02:07,168
I feel okay,
but it's a pain in the butt, you know,

26
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:10,713
because I have my son take the tops
off water bottles all the time for me

27
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:12,132
because I can't turn them.

28
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:14,926
Kind of embarrassing in a little way.

29
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:18,138
But it's all good, huh?

30
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:20,223
-Ain't that bad.
-Could be worse.

31
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,851
-I don't know. It's part of the deal, man.
-Yeah.

32
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:24,269
-You know?
-Keep you humble.

33
00:02:24,352 --> 00:02:26,980
It keeps me humble.
Keeps me very grateful.

34
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:30,108
In my mind,
I still think I'm 35 or 40 years old,

35
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:33,528
but as soon as I look in the mirror,
I go, "Who the hell's that?"

36
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:39,576
Getting down here
is like the only real peace in my life.

37
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:44,914
Once I'd get in that ring,
I wouldn't worry about kids, wives,

38
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:49,335
bills, problems, legal, criminal.

39
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:51,087
Any type of problems.

40
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:55,258
But I don't have that anymore.

41
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:59,387
In wrestling, you should be remembered
from the wars you've been in

42
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:00,972
and everything you've done.

43
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:08,855
And a lot of that's been taken away
in the last 20 years.

44
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:12,233
Was there a sinister side to his success?

45
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:14,861
Today, the WWE announced
they were dropping Hogan.

46
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:18,156
Hulk Hogan fired by the WWE…

47
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:21,534
I think he's a liar.
I think he's a coward.

48
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:23,244
There's certainly some things

49
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:26,956
that you would want to be remembered for
more than others, right?

50
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:31,085
Yeah.

51
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:33,296
Of course.

52
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:42,055
I think people wanna know the truth.

53
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:45,558
-Who was this guy, really?
-Is Hulk in the building?

54
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:47,644
Look what I'm married to.

55
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:49,646
Yeah, yeah.

56
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,315
I believe in what I'm doing,
and people get behind that.

57
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:55,318
They get behind me.
They know I train, pray, eat my vitamins.

58
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:57,862
If you say your prayers,
if you eat your vitamins, man,

59
00:03:57,946 --> 00:03:59,697
sooner or later, you get what you want.

60
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:00,698
This is serious.

61
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:03,034
Come on, Hulk!

62
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:05,828
Ridin' down the highway

63
00:04:07,163 --> 00:04:08,706
Goin' to a show

64
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:11,042
Beach-boy blonde, his body of bronze,

65
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:14,003
standing 6'9", and weighing 345.

66
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,755
His name is Hulk Hogan.

67
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:18,216
When you were born, they didn't say,

68
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:21,344
"This looks like a baby Hulk.
We'll name him Hulk Hogan."

69
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:24,472
No, but I grew into the name,
that's for sure.

70
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:29,185
What you gonna do
when Hulkamania runs wild on you?

71
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:32,897
It's a long way to the top
If you wanna rock 'n' roll…

72
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,566
Today, he is
the biggest name in wrestling.

73
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:38,403
It's a long way to the top…

74
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:42,156
One of the most famous
athletes in the history of the world.

75
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:47,328
Man, it feels great
to be on top of the mountain!

76
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:50,415
It feels like I got
about a million volts of electricity

77
00:04:50,498 --> 00:04:52,500
running through these 24-inch pythons!

78
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:53,876
Hulkster rules, brother.

79
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:57,213
A man who calls himself the ultimate male.

80
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,382
The ultimate all-American.

81
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:02,176
Here in America, you gotta work hard,
love hard, and die hard, man.

82
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:05,096
Such a long way

83
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:14,981
I can't predict and tell you right now

84
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:17,108
what the final act
of the story is gonna be.

85
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:33,291
I'm not looking for a legacy
pat on the back, for sure.

86
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,794
Not everyone is going to love you.

87
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:42,175
Some people hate me, but…

88
00:05:44,135 --> 00:05:46,637
I'm definitely the greatest wrestler
of all time.

89
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:47,638
I'm Hulk Hogan.

90
00:05:47,722 --> 00:05:49,932
Mr. Hulk Hogan!

91
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:53,227
Here he is, Hulk Hogan!

92
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,146
The man who needs no introduction.

93
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:57,106
-Hogan!
-Would you welcome Hulk Hogan?

94
00:05:59,275 --> 00:06:00,735
I'm Hulk Hogan.

95
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:14,540
Let's see if I can get through another day
and listen to myself talk.

96
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:16,376
Good grief.

97
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:18,753
Moments away. Makeup and hair, please.

98
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:22,382
"I'm here. I can do this."

99
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:24,217
"Couple of frizzies here, Hulk."

100
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,468
"Thank you, dear."

101
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,555
Fans recognize Hulk Hogan as a hero.

102
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:31,516
He's bigger than life.

103
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:35,061
A real hero who gives his all
for all the right reasons.

104
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:45,988
But I'm very aware now,
after all these years,

105
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:51,035
what that Hulk Hogan presence means,
um, you know, to the fans.

106
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,622
"I was not a mere mortal man."

107
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:57,708
"I was the superhero Hulk Hogan,"
when I had my stature.

108
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:01,003
The Hulk Hogan character is over the top.

109
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,630
It's a fake character.

110
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:06,217
You know, hopefully people
can understand that someday.

111
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:10,138
Man, I say my prayers, take my vitamins,
and everything I do is positive.

112
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:14,142
But, yeah, it's two different people.
You know, it's like me playing Dracula.

113
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:16,352
I don't come home
and bite my wife in the neck

114
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,438
and suck the blood out of my kids' necks.

115
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:21,065
But, duh, if you want
to believe that, go ahead.

116
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:22,483
But when I come in the house,

117
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:25,153
the headband comes off,
the bald head's there,

118
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:27,447
and my wife calls me Terry.

119
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,908
-Terry! Why do you do that?
-Watch this.

120
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:32,743
Terry won't leave this part out.

121
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:36,664
We're going to take some movies of Terry,
and we're going to make a video.

122
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:39,375
There were only a handful of people
knew him as Terry.

123
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,627
I knew him deeply as himself.

124
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:43,838
Oh my God, look at this.
We were always tan.

125
00:07:43,921 --> 00:07:45,673
I turned Terry on to a tanning bed.

126
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:48,593
He didn't even know what they were,
and he had to stay tanned for work.

127
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:50,595
Oop, Terry's naked.

128
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:56,476
You've broken every code…

129
00:07:57,518 --> 00:08:01,981
The fans just liked believing
that Hulk was like Superman.

130
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,691
Drop it out there! One…

131
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:06,819
You spoiled the game…

132
00:08:06,903 --> 00:08:08,196
-Hey!
-I know him.

133
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:10,072
When you're with somebody that long,

134
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:14,327
through thick and thin, good and bad,
tired, happy, sad, you know,

135
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:16,704
you learn that person very well.

136
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:19,749
Ooh, la-la-la

137
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:22,543
And I was always the one with the camera.

138
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:25,505
This is the, uh, greatest wall,

139
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:27,840
because the greatest person
is on this wall.

140
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:30,301
When I met Terry, I asked,
"Do you have family?"

141
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:32,887
He laid out his situation.

142
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:35,640
Let's show these people the refrigerator

143
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:40,269
that took me from a mere 196 pounds
when I was 12 years old

144
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:43,481
to a whopping 305-pound Hulk Hogan.

145
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:46,734
I grew up in Florida, in South Tampa.

146
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:50,696
We were broke, and I hated it.

147
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:56,827
Especially watching how my dad slaved
in the sun as a construction worker.

148
00:08:56,911 --> 00:08:59,330
-These old broken steps, man.
-Yeah.

149
00:08:59,413 --> 00:09:05,253
As a kid, I made a decision
that financially I'd never live like that.

150
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,964
We got Pete Bollea.

151
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:10,758
My dad was that old,
hard-school Italian, you know.

152
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:13,803
And he was a little rough on me,
that's for sure.

153
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:16,931
They weren't the type of parents
that would tell you they love you.

154
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:18,349
That would never happen.

155
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:20,434
Terry was a mistake-type child.

156
00:09:21,018 --> 00:09:24,939
They had Allan,
and then eight years later, had Terry.

157
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:28,693
My older brother, Allan,
he was the tough guy.

158
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:30,152
Allan was my dad's favorite.

159
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,280
He was always talking
about how strong he was,

160
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:36,659
and he would just tell me, you know,
"You're not like your brother," you know?

161
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:40,079
I didn't understand that
and always had a big chip on my shoulder.

162
00:09:41,038 --> 00:09:43,541
But, you know, I hated confrontations.

163
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,878
He wasn't the loudmouth you see on TV.

164
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:50,631
He was very soft-spoken, shy.

165
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:53,009
No, I wasn't always this confident.

166
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:55,011
When did that change?

167
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,471
On the weekends,

168
00:09:57,555 --> 00:10:01,142
Florida Championship Wrestling
would come on the TV back then.

169
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:04,353
I'd never seen anything like that.

170
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:13,279
I had no idea that this existed.

171
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:18,075
I was probably 8 or 9 years old
when we first went in person.

172
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:22,913
They had these great characters,
the conflict between good and bad,

173
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:26,876
how into it the fans were,
they were loyal, dedicated fans.

174
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:28,878
I love it! I love it!

175
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:32,381
There was this love and energy
that they were all getting there.

176
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,466
I could feel it, man.

177
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:37,887
And the one guy that really hooked me
was "The American Dream," Dusty Rhodes.

178
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:40,473
Truly, the idol of the people,
"The American Dream."

179
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:42,933
His whole rap reeled us in.

180
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:46,270
The razzmatazz,
my new Flandango waltz hold.

181
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:50,149
I'm so quick, I'm so fast,
Terry Funk is nothing but a punk.

182
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:53,527
The energy
would just drag you up out of any hole.

183
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:56,113
I went there all through childhood.

184
00:10:57,448 --> 00:10:58,491
I was hooked.

185
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:03,954
That's what I wanted to do.

186
00:11:05,956 --> 00:11:07,708
I wanted to be a wrestler.

187
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:14,215
The problem was
I was scared to death of those guys.

188
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:17,176
Most of them were 300 pounds and over,

189
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:20,054
and they had teeth knocked out
and broken noses and cauliflower ears.

190
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:22,640
It scared the bejesus out of me.

191
00:11:22,723 --> 00:11:26,477
I believed professional wrestling
was completely real.

192
00:11:27,978 --> 00:11:29,522
I knew I couldn't do it.

193
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:31,524
I was real fat.

194
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:35,027
Didn't take my shirt off, ever,
when I went to the beach

195
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:36,237
because I needed a bra.

196
00:11:37,154 --> 00:11:42,159
Pretty much, I was living off, you know,
Burger King and Snickers bars.

197
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:44,829
Played Little League baseball.

198
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:49,375
But they could throw me out at second.
I was so fat and slow.

199
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:51,502
So I got into bowling.

200
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:58,884
But then my life changed when I realized
I could make money playing music.

201
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:04,432
Terry was a talented bass player.

202
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:07,685
He would have been Guns N' Roses,
like, he's that level.

203
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:14,984
I learned that I liked being
in front of the crowd and being on stage.

204
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:18,320
But my dad was upset
that I had quit school

205
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:20,865
and was running around
in a rock and roll band

206
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:23,367
and lifting weights like an idiot.

207
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:27,872
It led to me, you know,
having a big blow out with my parents

208
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:29,373
and getting kicked out of the house.

209
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,751
You got it

210
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:36,672
So, a few years after high school,
we had a little following in North Tampa.

211
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:39,884
Then all of a sudden,
these wrestlers were coming in the bar.

212
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:42,803
Oh my gosh,
I'm on stage, and here's these guys.

213
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:45,973
I'm scared to death of guys
like "Superstar" Billy Graham.

214
00:12:46,056 --> 00:12:48,058
You know what a fist sandwich is?

215
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:50,102
And Brian Blair.

216
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:54,940
My first memory of meeting Terry
was when he was playing bass guitar,

217
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:56,442
and he'd stand out so much.

218
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:59,153
He was in these platform heels
and had jewelry on,

219
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:02,740
and long blonde hair, suntan, big muscles.

220
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,325
I mean, he was the show.

221
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:06,827
The music was good,
but he was, like, the show.

222
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:10,790
What shocked me more than anything
was that they weren't mean to me.

223
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,795
I didn't realize they were grooming me.

224
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:21,509
And they took me to all the matches,
so I could get in free.

225
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:30,726
And then one of the biggest nights
of my life changed everything.

226
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:35,606
We saw Steve Keirn
at Fort Homer Hesterly Armory.

227
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:42,822
The bad guy was just waylaying his ass,
and the referee told him to knock it off.

228
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:45,616
"Let go of me, ref."

229
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:48,410
I remember he looked right down
at Steve Keirn.

230
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,538
I read his lips.

231
00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:53,249
He said, "Hit me. Hit me."

232
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,875
I went, "What?"

233
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:56,335
And Steve hit him.

234
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,629
And he goes, "Again, again."

235
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:02,258
And he made this comeback from underneath.
I was like, "What?!"

236
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:04,093
I just didn't believe it.

237
00:14:05,052 --> 00:14:08,514
I was disillusioned for about two seconds,
and I got over it.

238
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:10,850
All of a sudden, the door opens

239
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:14,728
and I knew I didn't have to be a tough guy
to get in the business.

240
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:21,443
They don't want to tell you
that it's not real.

241
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,863
They want you to believe that it is.

242
00:14:25,739 --> 00:14:30,411
But people don't realize
what your body goes through.

243
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:33,789
You get your butt kicked
in professional wrestling.

244
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:44,550
Wow.

245
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:48,012
I remember all too well.

246
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:51,265
This is where
Terry and I learned to wrestle.

247
00:14:51,348 --> 00:14:53,100
It was called The Dungeon.

248
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:05,195
And I just believed that I knew exactly
what I had to do to run with the pack.

249
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:08,032
It was brutal. Brutal.

250
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:10,284
What you had to go through
to get into the business.

251
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:14,455
The newer guys, they have no clue.
They have no clue.

252
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:17,791
I spent a year in the gym
training twice a day

253
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,336
and laying in the sun all day long.

254
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:24,590
And like a fool, I told everybody
I was going to be a wrestler.

255
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:27,593
"I'm going to be a wrestler."
That's the wrong thing to do.

256
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:30,137
One of the teachers
put his forearm in my shin

257
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:32,056
and grabbed my toe, snap.

258
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:36,310
And they broke his leg,
literally broke it.

259
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:42,274
I was living in a hotel room at the time.

260
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:43,817
Um…

261
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:47,613
I tried to come home whenever I could,
but I wasn't welcome there, you know.

262
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:52,034
When my dad would go to work,
I'd run back to the house.

263
00:15:52,117 --> 00:15:53,160
Sweetheart.

264
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:55,329
My mom would cook for me
and take care of me.

265
00:15:55,412 --> 00:15:57,373
Then I could sleep in his bed.

266
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,709
"You gotta get outta here.
Your dad's coming home." So I'd take off.

267
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:04,213
You know, my leg getting broke

268
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,799
was minuscule
compared to what he put me through, so.

269
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:08,717
Bang, bang, bang!

270
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:11,887
I had to go back.
There was no quitting for me.

271
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:17,810
As soon as I got better,
I started showing up down there.

272
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:21,939
That made Terry want to try even harder.

273
00:16:22,022 --> 00:16:23,774
Like, "You're not gonna keep me down."

274
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:29,530
He just was like a Timex.
He took the licking and kept on ticking.

275
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:31,281
Bang on.

276
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:34,201
That's Terry.
That's the Hulkster. That's him.

277
00:16:39,164 --> 00:16:41,792
Terry's first match was against me.

278
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:45,879
He came out with a mask on
as the Super Destroyer.

279
00:16:46,922 --> 00:16:47,965
And he looked dorky.

280
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:50,050
Super Destroyer!

281
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:55,889
Terry Bollea did not complete his training

282
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:57,933
and immediately become Hulk Hogan.

283
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:02,271
I mean, you have to pay your dues,
and you have to develop your persona.

284
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:07,192
I'm a professional wrestling historian
and author.

285
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:09,403
And despite my youthful appearance,

286
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:13,699
I've been covering the sport of kings
for more than 40 years.

287
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:20,581
Terry Bollea's youth and his size
made you take notice.

288
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:22,583
He had genetic gifts.

289
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:26,670
The Super Destroyer was masked,
and I believe that was deliberate.

290
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:27,963
I was getting beat everywhere.

291
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,923
They didn't want
people to see me getting beat.

292
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:32,509
I had to learn how to work in the ring.

293
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:37,848
This is someone
who had the potential to be a notable.

294
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:40,642
But he wasn't there yet.
He was very green.

295
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:44,188
Put the guy under a mask.
Let him make his mistakes.

296
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:47,441
Later on,
we can make him into a real character.

297
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,659
Oh my God.

298
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:00,746
Wrestling was very territorial back then.

299
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:03,957
Like the American mob,

300
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:07,461
professional wrestling promoters
formed an organization

301
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:12,508
that would divide
North America into territories.

302
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:15,010
You're supposed to stay
six or seven months in each place,

303
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,261
then get your bags and move.

304
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:22,017
I was driving like 25,
26 hundred miles a week.

305
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:31,568
I was finally, you know,
trading a real life for a wrestling life.

306
00:18:35,572 --> 00:18:37,116
So I went up to Memphis.

307
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:40,828
Forgot my six-string razor…

308
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,329
And I took off the mask.

309
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:43,705
Hit the sky…

310
00:18:43,789 --> 00:18:46,125
And changed my name to be Terry Boulder.

311
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:49,670
Halfway to Memphis 'fore I realized

312
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:55,300
Well, I rang the information…

313
00:18:55,384 --> 00:18:57,928
Gonna have to buy a ticket
to see my face, brother.

314
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:00,347
Come in the ring,
full head of blonde hair.

315
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:03,058
Largest arms in the world.
Largest back in the world.

316
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:06,937
He's rock solid like a boulder,
so it's a good name.

317
00:19:07,020 --> 00:19:11,483
That's Terry Boulder,
295 pounds, from Tampa.

318
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:13,861
Oh, slammed by Boulder.

319
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:18,115
And this Monday night in Memphis,
Daddy, when I get a hold of you,

320
00:19:18,198 --> 00:19:20,659
I'm gonna take you and bury your head
right in the mat, brother.

321
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:22,911
I'm gonna teach you
a bit of a wrestling lesson,

322
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:25,038
a little respect
for these good people here.

323
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:27,708
I'm gonna put
the super southern squeeze on you, Daddy.

324
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:31,086
"I'm Terry Boulder, and when I get
this super southern squeeze on you,

325
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,505
it'll be lights out for you
and whoever's around."

326
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:36,633
And I was talking like that.
I mean, seriously.

327
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:40,470
Hulk Hogan didn't exist yet.

328
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:47,394
First time I saw Hulk,
I really wasn't in the wrestling business.

329
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:49,771
That happened years later.

330
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,190
Come on in.

331
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:54,735
Can you believe a WWE Hall of Famer

332
00:19:54,818 --> 00:19:58,906
sitting out here waiting all day for you
to get here? This is too much. Too much!

333
00:19:58,989 --> 00:20:01,867
Here is
"The Mouth of the South," Jimmy Hart.

334
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:03,744
Come on, show him what it's all about.

335
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:06,079
Show him what it's all about,
Mega-Maniacs!

336
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:07,372
Can you believe this?

337
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:11,501
Jimmy Hart, manager of Hulk Hogan.

338
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,545
To the fans, I was Hulk's manager.

339
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:17,341
Wrestling manager,
not real, real, real, real manager.

340
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:19,927
You've been wearing
that outfit since 1983.

341
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:21,261
And I'll always wear it.

342
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:22,804
-I'm done with you.
-Done?

343
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,473
-Let's talk to Hulk.
-Jimmy!

344
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:26,558
Oh my God.

345
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:30,771
I want to talk about Jimmy Hart!
You wanna talk about and mess about?

346
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:34,858
If it wasn't for two people in my life,
Jerry Lawler and Hulk Hogan,

347
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:37,986
there'd be no Jimmy Hart.
Trust me on that, and I really mean that.

348
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:42,950
I went to high school with
Jerry "The King" Lawler, back in Memphis.

349
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,243
To the wrestling fans,

350
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:47,079
there was nobody bigger
than Jerry "The King" Lawler.

351
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:50,040
Jerry "The King" Lawler!

352
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:54,169
And I remember one night,
I went by the Coliseum to see wrestling.

353
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:56,713
Jerry Lawler goes, "Jimmy, come here."
I said, "What is it?"

354
00:20:56,797 --> 00:20:59,091
He goes, "You see that guy?"
I went, "Yeah."

355
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:01,593
"What do you think?"
I went, "Wow, man, unbelievable."

356
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:04,054
"What do they call him?"
He said, "Terry Boulder."

357
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,890
And I went, "God, he looks great."

358
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:08,850
He goes, "He asked me to manage him."

359
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:11,353
I said, "You gonna do it?"
He said, "Are you kidding?"

360
00:21:11,436 --> 00:21:13,355
"This guy'll never make a dime
in this business."

361
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:17,776
He was not very good.
I'll be honest with you.

362
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:22,948
Hogan was very big, of course.
Everybody knew that.

363
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:26,702
But not on the same level
as other wrestlers.

364
00:21:26,785 --> 00:21:29,204
He was just kind of getting his feet wet.

365
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:32,249
I started making $800 a week.

366
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:35,419
You needed to make at least $1,000
to buy food and gas

367
00:21:35,502 --> 00:21:37,629
and pay for hotel rooms back then.

368
00:21:41,216 --> 00:21:42,843
One thing I told him,

369
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:46,013
"You need to take a punch,
but you don't need to take a bump."

370
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:50,058
"You just stand there and overcome that
with your size and your strength."

371
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:52,185
-In the elbow!
-Not doing much damage.

372
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:54,980
The amazing size of this Terry Boulder,

373
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:58,150
truly one of the greats
in professional wrestling.

374
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,193
He was super green.

375
00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:03,697
I wrestled him in Atlanta
quite a few times in that period.

376
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:07,993
About to enter the ring,
Bret "The Hitman" Hart.

377
00:22:09,661 --> 00:22:12,414
And the match was always
about 30 seconds long.

378
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:15,751
Maybe you people don't realize
what you're looking at, Daddy.

379
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:19,504
But you got 6'7" right here,
a mountain of a man.

380
00:22:19,588 --> 00:22:22,632
I knew more about wrestling then
than he knew in his whole life.

381
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:24,468
Anybody who wants to step in the ring,

382
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:28,430
I have $1,000 up for anybody
who can break the golden squeeze.

383
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:30,891
All it was was a bear hug.
That's all he could do.

384
00:22:31,475 --> 00:22:35,812
Oh, what a night it's gonna be

385
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:39,274
Look at that.
Look at that. Can you believe that?

386
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:42,652
Now with him
in the air like a piece of meat,

387
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:45,072
and a bear hug,
I suspect we'll hear the submission.

388
00:22:45,155 --> 00:22:47,324
-Yes, indeed.
-Amazing!

389
00:22:47,407 --> 00:22:49,826
That's all he needed to do.
It was believable enough.

390
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:53,705
It was a sight to see a guy like that
squeeze the daylights out of you,

391
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:56,166
and throw you down on the mat
and walk around.

392
00:22:57,459 --> 00:23:00,921
He was unbeatable. He was just so big.

393
00:23:01,004 --> 00:23:03,465
He really didn't look like a human being.

394
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:08,220
He looked like somebody
who did step out of a comic book.

395
00:23:10,931 --> 00:23:15,352
At that point, all the promoters,
they said, "You're bigger than The Hulk."

396
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:20,273
A big muscular monster,
so that's a good name.

397
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:23,068
And that's where
Terry "The Hulk" Boulder started.

398
00:23:23,151 --> 00:23:27,197
Oh, there's that big leg. Huge man.

399
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:28,448
First thing I did was

400
00:23:28,532 --> 00:23:33,203
I did a video standing
on Jerry Jarrett's kitchen room table.

401
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:35,497
When they see this guy,

402
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:37,541
they won't forget
that Terry Boulder is The Hulk.

403
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:39,292
Let's take a look at it right now.

404
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:43,630
This man is not a television illusion.

405
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:48,593
He is not an artist's conception.

406
00:23:49,344 --> 00:23:53,473
He is not a figment of the imagination.

407
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:57,060
He is real.

408
00:23:58,145 --> 00:24:00,897
He is The Hulk.

409
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:07,237
That made him into a superhero.
It really did.

410
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:11,658
"He's The Hulk." It's… It was terrible.

411
00:24:11,741 --> 00:24:15,954
Not a lot was expected from Hulk Hogan
in terms of character.

412
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:20,876
He was intriguing,
and they wanted to see more of him.

413
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:23,753
-And here comes.
-Terry "The Hulk" Boulder.

414
00:24:23,837 --> 00:24:26,506
I'd show up. They put me
in the main event everywhere we go.

415
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:32,846
The character didn't really have a persona
other than he was big and nasty and mean.

416
00:24:35,307 --> 00:24:39,144
We have a confrontation now.
We could have some problems here and now.

417
00:24:39,227 --> 00:24:41,021
Everybody's been running scared.

418
00:24:41,104 --> 00:24:44,399
They've been feeding me this Grade B meat
every week on TV.

419
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:46,610
I want the best now.

420
00:24:46,693 --> 00:24:50,780
All these superstars who have been hiding
in the eye of the storm, brother.

421
00:24:50,864 --> 00:24:52,282
I've been whipping everybody.

422
00:24:52,365 --> 00:24:55,994
As I was becoming more popular,
all the promoters, they said,

423
00:24:56,077 --> 00:25:00,081
"With your look and as big as you are,
you need to be in New York."

424
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:05,462
Madison Square Garden
is the epitome of wrestling.

425
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:10,800
"There was a guy
named Vince McMahon Sr. who called."

426
00:25:13,094 --> 00:25:14,596
"And he wants you to come to New York."

427
00:25:17,766 --> 00:25:19,518
So I went up there,

428
00:25:19,601 --> 00:25:22,938
and Vince McMahon's clicking quarters,
looking at me.

429
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:27,067
"I want you to come to work for me,
work nothing but main events,

430
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:28,777
and draw money all over the world."

431
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:29,819
I said, "Oh, really?"

432
00:25:31,071 --> 00:25:34,241
"First off, I would change the name."

433
00:25:34,908 --> 00:25:39,329
Here is "The Incredible" Hulk Hogan!

434
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:44,167
And I said, "What is a Hulk Hogan?"
What does that mean?

435
00:25:44,876 --> 00:25:47,128
Back in the day,
my dad gave him his name.

436
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:48,255
He was this big kid,

437
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:51,383
and my dad, of course, being Irish,
decided Hogan is a great name.

438
00:25:51,466 --> 00:25:53,093
So why not Hulk Hogan?

439
00:25:53,176 --> 00:25:55,887
It was alliterative,
so let's go with that.

440
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,142
Vince said, "Doesn't matter to me."

441
00:26:01,768 --> 00:26:03,728
"Yeah, okay, I'll think about it."

442
00:26:05,564 --> 00:26:10,694
His opponent makes
his Madison Square Garden debut,

443
00:26:10,777 --> 00:26:14,990
"The Incredible" Hulk Hogan!

444
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:19,494
The very first match that Hulk Hogan
ever had at Madison Square Garden

445
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:22,038
was with yours truly, Ted DiBiase.

446
00:26:22,122 --> 00:26:27,294
Here is "The Million Dollar Man,"
Ted DiBiase!

447
00:26:29,879 --> 00:26:30,964
Money, money

448
00:26:32,799 --> 00:26:35,135
Ted DiBiase!

449
00:26:35,802 --> 00:26:38,430
When Hulk and I had that match,

450
00:26:38,513 --> 00:26:42,183
Vince McMahon Sr. came to me, and he said,

451
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:45,103
"We have really high hopes for this guy."

452
00:26:45,186 --> 00:26:48,732
"I really want you to get him over
as best you can."

453
00:26:48,815 --> 00:26:51,192
Putting someone over means he's gonna win.

454
00:26:51,318 --> 00:26:54,029
And I said, "You got it, boss."

455
00:26:54,112 --> 00:26:57,991
He was brand new.
He was obviously just still learning.

456
00:26:58,074 --> 00:27:01,077
But my job was
to make him look really good.

457
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:05,290
When we first locked up,
you know, he powers out.

458
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:07,709
And Hogan breaks the full-nelson.

459
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:09,878
Hogan is playing the strength
for which he is noted.

460
00:27:09,961 --> 00:27:12,339
I back up into the corner like,
"Oh my gosh."

461
00:27:14,049 --> 00:27:18,053
You know, I'm trying to convey
to the people that, you know,

462
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:21,014
what do I have to do to get this guy down?

463
00:27:21,097 --> 00:27:23,516
DiBiase tries it again. Oh God!

464
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:26,895
For this to be the forefront
of the wrestling business,

465
00:27:26,978 --> 00:27:29,439
the main event in Madison Square Garden,

466
00:27:29,522 --> 00:27:31,983
the beginning of a whole new era,

467
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:34,444
I thought I had arrived.

468
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:45,747
Ted DiBiase. Now he has him in a bear hug.

469
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:47,374
And it could be over.

470
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:50,085
That's over.

471
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:53,588
He was a heel. He beats me.

472
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,715
I was the good guy, and they booed him.

473
00:27:55,799 --> 00:27:57,967
They booed him out of the building.

474
00:28:00,053 --> 00:28:02,097
Victorious in his very first appearance

475
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:04,099
here in Madison Square Garden.

476
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,768
And, uh, I started running my mouth.

477
00:28:06,851 --> 00:28:08,603
Everybody is looking for an idol.

478
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:14,317
From now on, I wish to be referred to,
and I demand to be referred to

479
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:16,569
as the superhero Hulk Hogan.

480
00:28:16,653 --> 00:28:19,698
I knew I would be a bad guy,
and I was really good at it.

481
00:28:20,824 --> 00:28:23,952
We're now going to talk to Hulk Hogan.

482
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:27,122
These people
want to know what Hulk Hogan's all about.

483
00:28:27,205 --> 00:28:30,291
I start out every day
by looking in the mirror

484
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:33,545
and saying, "Good morning, Mr. Hulk Hogan.
I'm happy to see you again."

485
00:28:33,628 --> 00:28:37,716
I would rather see myself in the morning
than somebody ugly like you.

486
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:40,760
You don't like to brag very much, do you?

487
00:28:40,844 --> 00:28:42,095
Not a bit, not at all.

488
00:28:42,679 --> 00:28:47,183
Magazine offers, television appearances,
they're all coming in now.

489
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:49,227
I am the new superhero.

490
00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:56,317
Then one day, they brought me this note,
"Please call Sylvester Stallone,"

491
00:28:56,401 --> 00:28:59,320
about a cameo role in a Rocky movie.

492
00:29:02,532 --> 00:29:03,992
I'll be darned.

493
00:29:04,075 --> 00:29:06,286
Who's the fellow that you do this with?

494
00:29:06,369 --> 00:29:07,537
His name is Hulk Hogan.

495
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:10,874
He is a fellow
that I saw one night on television.

496
00:29:10,957 --> 00:29:12,250
I was laying… Had insomnia,

497
00:29:12,333 --> 00:29:15,295
and he came on and beat up four wrestlers
at the same time.

498
00:29:15,378 --> 00:29:18,590
And he was a giant,
about 7 feet tall, about 350 pounds.

499
00:29:18,673 --> 00:29:21,926
But then I told Mr. McMahon
I was leaving Fall River that night

500
00:29:22,010 --> 00:29:23,428
to fly to LA to film the movie.

501
00:29:23,511 --> 00:29:26,639
He goes, "No, you're not.
You need to drive all night."

502
00:29:26,723 --> 00:29:29,184
Because I had to be
on Charlotte TV at noon.

503
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:32,437
I said, "No, Mr. McMahon, I told you
I was gonna do the Rocky movie."

504
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:34,856
He goes,
"If you do the movie, you're fired."

505
00:29:35,523 --> 00:29:39,360
And I had a great rapport with him.
We'd talk all the time.

506
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:42,655
It was like a father-son thing.
He'd talk me down off the ledge.

507
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:46,034
But I just knew I had to do it.

508
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:49,621
He said, "You'll never work here again."
I went, "Okay, cool." Click.

509
00:29:52,373 --> 00:29:55,084
Are you really gonna fight that wrestler?
They're so big.

510
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:56,377
That's all right. It'll be fun.

511
00:29:56,461 --> 00:29:58,671
Tonight we have
a most unlikely match for you.

512
00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:00,799
The boxer against the wrestler.

513
00:30:00,882 --> 00:30:05,303
I remember seeing Rocky III
in the theater twice in the same week.

514
00:30:05,386 --> 00:30:08,056
I felt it was a slap in the face

515
00:30:08,139 --> 00:30:12,602
to everybody who made fun of me
for being a wrestling fan.

516
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:16,856
Now they knew what they were missing.

517
00:30:16,940 --> 00:30:19,234
They could see it
right there on the big screen.

518
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:22,028
Here we go, baby. Lights out!

519
00:30:22,111 --> 00:30:24,239
The general public all of a sudden went,

520
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:28,117
"Oh my God, is that
what a professional wrestler looks like?"

521
00:30:28,201 --> 00:30:30,119
"Is that what professional wrestling is?"

522
00:30:30,203 --> 00:30:32,288
-That's a large person.
-Okay.

523
00:30:32,372 --> 00:30:36,709
And he eats 5'10" Italians.

524
00:30:37,418 --> 00:30:39,462
We ought to get that guy on the show.

525
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:43,591
I'd already shot the Stallone movie.

526
00:30:44,884 --> 00:30:47,387
I was there to do
the Johnny Carson show or something.

527
00:30:47,470 --> 00:30:49,389
Would you welcome Hulk Hogan?

528
00:30:49,889 --> 00:30:52,267
Looking at the size of your arms,
I don't believe this.

529
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:54,727
I wish I had anything that big.

530
00:30:58,982 --> 00:31:01,109
-How about your bank account?
-Bank? No.

531
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:03,820
And me and my buddy went to the Red Onion.

532
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:09,576
The very first time I saw him,
it was in the Valley at the Red Onion.

533
00:31:09,659 --> 00:31:12,328
Rocky III had just come out,

534
00:31:13,121 --> 00:31:15,915
and Terry was playing
the part of Thunderlips, right?

535
00:31:15,999 --> 00:31:19,085
And all of a sudden,
there was Thunderlips, baby, in the flesh…

536
00:31:19,168 --> 00:31:20,962
…coming into my bar,

537
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:23,214
and I'm looking, I'm thinking,
"This can't be happening."

538
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:24,924
"I just saw the movie last night."

539
00:31:25,008 --> 00:31:26,801
Thunderlips is here!

540
00:31:27,302 --> 00:31:28,845
In the flesh, baby!

541
00:31:29,596 --> 00:31:30,930
The ultimate male!

542
00:31:32,515 --> 00:31:35,184
There's this little posse of chicks
all around him, right?

543
00:31:35,268 --> 00:31:36,728
All these girls all around him.

544
00:31:36,811 --> 00:31:38,730
Like, they're touching muscles and shit.

545
00:31:38,813 --> 00:31:42,817
He just kind of stood there
and just sort of, like, flexed and stuff,

546
00:31:42,901 --> 00:31:44,986
and I was like,
"That's cool, I like that."

547
00:31:45,069 --> 00:31:46,070
Oh my God.

548
00:31:46,154 --> 00:31:48,907
It was very intriguing
to be around somebody like that.

549
00:31:49,699 --> 00:31:51,743
All of a sudden, Linda came walking,

550
00:31:51,826 --> 00:31:56,706
and it was like everything stopped,
because everybody in the bar watched her.

551
00:31:56,789 --> 00:32:02,253
It was like every single person in the bar
watched her walk across the room.

552
00:32:02,337 --> 00:32:04,339
It was like,
"Oh my God, that girl's gorgeous."

553
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:06,758
And I said, "Holy smokes."

554
00:32:07,342 --> 00:32:11,471
And the second
that my foot hit the dance floor,

555
00:32:11,554 --> 00:32:13,181
I felt this arm come on me.

556
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:14,933
It was as big as my thigh.

557
00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:16,351
"Do you want to dance?"

558
00:32:16,434 --> 00:32:19,395
"Aren't you that guy in the Rocky movie?"
I said, "I am."

559
00:32:19,479 --> 00:32:23,900
She goes, "Oh, yeah, you're Mr. T."
I went, "No, I'm not Mr. T."

560
00:32:23,983 --> 00:32:26,611
He was like, "It's Hulk Hogan."
I was like, "Hunk Hogan?"

561
00:32:26,694 --> 00:32:30,823
I thought his name was Hunk Hogan.
Who would call themselves Hunk Hogan?

562
00:32:30,907 --> 00:32:34,869
I thought, "He's an actor."
And then he told me he was a wrestler.

563
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:37,080
And I said, "What… what is that?"

564
00:32:37,163 --> 00:32:40,041
He was like, "Well, you have
to experience it to comprehend it."

565
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:41,668
That was his answer was to me.

566
00:32:41,751 --> 00:32:44,170
I was like,
"All right, we'll see where that goes."

567
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:47,799
After that, he goes, "Let's go back
to the apartment where I'm staying."

568
00:32:48,591 --> 00:32:52,095
So we go up,
and it's this rickety-ass old apartment.

569
00:32:52,178 --> 00:32:54,555
He brings me a beer.
He's like, "I'll be right back."

570
00:32:54,639 --> 00:32:56,516
He goes in the bathroom, right?

571
00:32:56,599 --> 00:32:59,018
I'm waiting the longest time.

572
00:32:59,102 --> 00:33:02,397
All of a sudden, he comes out.
He's completely naked.

573
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:05,525
I'm like, "Well, say what you want
without saying what you want."

574
00:33:05,608 --> 00:33:09,529
It was like when you go to the zoo,
and you see, like, a mammy wooloth,

575
00:33:09,612 --> 00:33:12,323
or whatever they're called,
a woolly mammoth… He was huge.

576
00:33:12,407 --> 00:33:15,576
We drank a couple of bottles of wine
and just hit it off great.

577
00:33:15,660 --> 00:33:20,039
And how many people can say
they got fucked by a giant?

578
00:33:20,123 --> 00:33:22,667
And we were together ever since.

579
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:27,171
Love brought me such a magical thing…

580
00:33:27,255 --> 00:33:29,841
Hulk, just exactly how do you lock up?

581
00:33:29,924 --> 00:33:32,468
I'm training in the bedroom.
Goosebumps from head to toe.

582
00:33:32,552 --> 00:33:39,517
He was such a force of energy
and excitement and a new wave of life.

583
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:42,729
I, like, sort of got addicted quickly.

584
00:33:42,812 --> 00:33:46,107
All-star wrestling action continues,
a one-fall match.

585
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:48,192
"The Incredible" Hulk Hogan.

586
00:33:48,276 --> 00:33:50,403
When wrestling was just territorial,

587
00:33:50,486 --> 00:33:54,115
two of the big places
that everybody wanted to go was New York,

588
00:33:54,198 --> 00:33:55,450
where I'd just been fired.

589
00:33:58,953 --> 00:34:01,497
The other place
everybody wanted to go was Minnesota.

590
00:34:03,291 --> 00:34:07,045
Ladies and gentlemen,
from here in the Twin Cities, Minnesota…

591
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:10,298
So I sent
some 8x10 pictures from Rocky III

592
00:34:10,381 --> 00:34:13,301
to a promoter named Verne Gagne
in Minnesota.

593
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:16,304
I got a message back,
"How soon can you get here?"

594
00:34:16,804 --> 00:34:18,139
What a welcome.

595
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:21,309
The red carpet out for you,
"The Incredible" Hulk Hogan.

596
00:34:22,226 --> 00:34:26,481
When I went to Minnesota,
I came in as a bad guy, as a heel.

597
00:34:27,356 --> 00:34:28,649
If you'd like to face them

598
00:34:28,733 --> 00:34:31,903
and give our television audience
an opportunity of seeing you firsthand.

599
00:34:31,986 --> 00:34:33,321
I'll look any way I want.

600
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:36,991
They had a real popular wrestler there
named Jesse Ventura.

601
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:40,328
And so the whole thing was they wanted
me to come in and beat Jesse up.

602
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:42,413
I'm Jesse Ventura.

603
00:34:42,497 --> 00:34:45,875
Known in the world of wrestling
as Jesse "The Body" Ventura.

604
00:34:45,958 --> 00:34:49,879
He is Jesse "The Body" Ventura!

605
00:34:51,172 --> 00:34:55,635
Jesse "The Body" Ventura,
flamboyant, gregarious, outspoken.

606
00:34:55,718 --> 00:34:59,180
Let me tell you something, Chump Hogan,
you are not ready for me.

607
00:34:59,263 --> 00:35:01,182
I'm pumped up. I'm excited.

608
00:35:01,265 --> 00:35:02,558
You're bleeding, man.

609
00:35:02,642 --> 00:35:03,851
I ain't got time to bleed.

610
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:07,230
And also ended up a mayor and a governor.

611
00:35:07,313 --> 00:35:09,607
Governor Ventura has a new career.

612
00:35:09,690 --> 00:35:12,902
I learned in the world of pro wrestling,
you never say never.

613
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:15,446
The Rocky movie came out,

614
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:18,866
and he started getting
bigger, bigger, bigger.

615
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:23,996
"The Incredible" Hulk
taunting Jesse "The Body" Ventura.

616
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:26,290
They brought Hogan in as a villain.

617
00:35:27,083 --> 00:35:30,002
"The Incredible" Hulk.
Jesse "The Body" lets Hulk have one.

618
00:35:30,086 --> 00:35:32,046
Jesse looking over the crowd.

619
00:35:32,130 --> 00:35:34,674
The people really, in a way, turned Hulk.

620
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:39,470
Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk!

621
00:35:41,514 --> 00:35:43,641
The reception
was something no one had seen.

622
00:35:43,724 --> 00:35:45,434
Nobody had ever seen it.

623
00:35:45,518 --> 00:35:49,522
The crowd
all for the one and only Hulk Hogan.

624
00:35:49,605 --> 00:35:54,152
It was a great moment
because the fans were writing the plot.

625
00:35:54,235 --> 00:35:55,653
There's nothing else like it.

626
00:35:55,736 --> 00:35:57,947
That's why I fell in love
with the art form.

627
00:35:58,030 --> 00:36:01,534
The people wanted to cheer him.
People wanted a hero.

628
00:36:01,617 --> 00:36:03,870
The audiences throw that vibe out.

629
00:36:03,953 --> 00:36:06,622
They'll tell you
when to be evil and aggressive.

630
00:36:06,706 --> 00:36:07,999
Arm twist.

631
00:36:08,082 --> 00:36:09,292
Hulk! Hulk! Hulk!

632
00:36:09,375 --> 00:36:10,751
They'll tell you when to get even.

633
00:36:14,964 --> 00:36:16,340
Tell you when to turn it up.

634
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:22,430
Do you see what's happening?
The Hulk is coming alive, so is the crowd.

635
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:25,474
And they'll tell you
when to turn good guy.

636
00:36:27,518 --> 00:36:29,187
And Jesse into a bear hug!

637
00:36:32,148 --> 00:36:35,026
Out goes Ventura.
Hogan is right on his tail.

638
00:36:35,109 --> 00:36:37,528
This one is no contest.

639
00:36:38,905 --> 00:36:43,034
The Hulk driving his fist
to the head of Jesse "The Body" Ventura.

640
00:36:43,117 --> 00:36:45,536
Is Ventura going back to the locker room?

641
00:36:45,620 --> 00:36:47,205
It looks like he is.

642
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:48,789
I became the good guy.

643
00:36:48,873 --> 00:36:51,083
Hulk Hogan!

644
00:36:51,584 --> 00:36:54,086
His thousands
and thousands of fans are saying,

645
00:36:54,170 --> 00:36:55,296
"Hey, you're the one."

646
00:36:55,379 --> 00:36:59,842
This is the happiest day in all my life.
Once I was a sinner, and now I'm a saint.

647
00:36:59,926 --> 00:37:03,387
The reason is because of Dusty Rhodes.
Dusty Rhodes, "The American Dream."

648
00:37:03,471 --> 00:37:06,098
Dreams that you saved up for a lifetime,

649
00:37:06,182 --> 00:37:10,186
and that's things
that you couldn't reach out and get.

650
00:37:10,269 --> 00:37:12,230
"The Dream" taught me
what it was all about.

651
00:37:12,313 --> 00:37:15,650
He taught me about loving, living,
fighting, and getting down to war.

652
00:37:15,733 --> 00:37:19,153
About ten years ago,
I left Tampa, Florida, my hometown,

653
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:21,239
with a big chip on my shoulder.

654
00:37:21,322 --> 00:37:25,368
I took on all the top contenders, Daddy.
And then the day of reckoning came.

655
00:37:27,119 --> 00:37:31,249
The only way to really grow
in the professional wrestling business

656
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:33,793
is to make yourself bigger.

657
00:37:33,876 --> 00:37:37,797
Not just physically bigger,
but bigger as a personality.

658
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,298
And that's what he did.

659
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:41,550
Man, oh, man.
What time is it, little dude?

660
00:37:41,634 --> 00:37:43,135
What time do you have right there, man?

661
00:37:43,219 --> 00:37:44,637
-Eight o'clock.
-Eight o'clock?

662
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:47,640
I feel like I've been awake
for 40 days and 40 nights, man.

663
00:37:47,723 --> 00:37:48,849
And the reason why…

664
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:50,059
He got it, you know?

665
00:37:50,142 --> 00:37:51,894
And it was crazy because I remember

666
00:37:51,978 --> 00:37:54,563
listening to him
kind of cut through a promo.

667
00:37:54,647 --> 00:37:57,650
Where does this redneck get off at?
Where does he get off at?

668
00:37:57,733 --> 00:38:00,778
He started getting creepy, and weird shit,
you know, and I'm like…

669
00:38:00,861 --> 00:38:04,490
And for one moment, I felt a power
like I've never felt before.

670
00:38:04,573 --> 00:38:05,825
A lightning bolt hit me.

671
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:07,326
He had a great promo.

672
00:38:07,410 --> 00:38:09,787
On a scale of one to ten,
Hulk Hogan was a ten.

673
00:38:09,870 --> 00:38:12,957
If your Richter scale
spins around three and four times,

674
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,250
it's not an earthquake.

675
00:38:14,333 --> 00:38:18,546
It's just me pressing that big Elijah
over my head in the Sun Dome.

676
00:38:18,629 --> 00:38:21,716
Hulk Hogan would talk
for 59 seconds exactly,

677
00:38:21,799 --> 00:38:23,759
and it was like, "Cut, that's a take."

678
00:38:23,843 --> 00:38:27,096
I don't like to overthink things.
There's nothing to think about either.

679
00:38:27,179 --> 00:38:30,182
You either can dance and play the guitar
and play the fiddle, or you can't.

680
00:38:31,726 --> 00:38:32,893
At the age of 30,

681
00:38:32,977 --> 00:38:35,354
Hogan is one of the most colorful
good guys in the game.

682
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:37,523
I figured my entrance out.
I had the music.

683
00:38:37,606 --> 00:38:42,111
I had it really, really rocking,
if you watch the old Minnesota tapes.

684
00:38:42,903 --> 00:38:45,781
But I didn't have
the most important thing.

685
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:47,575
I needed a gimmick.

686
00:38:48,951 --> 00:38:50,745
He was a super smart guy.

687
00:38:50,828 --> 00:38:53,748
He could figure out the big picture
more than other people could.

688
00:38:54,623 --> 00:38:56,292
His wheels were turning,

689
00:38:56,375 --> 00:38:58,961
and the character
was never not on his mind.

690
00:38:59,045 --> 00:39:03,215
Whether it's a big guy, fat guy,
hairy guy, bodybuilder shape, whatever,

691
00:39:03,299 --> 00:39:06,344
a great gimmick
needs to transcend the wrestler.

692
00:39:06,427 --> 00:39:09,347
And patriotism back then meant everything.

693
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:14,727
USA! USA! USA! USA! USA!

694
00:39:17,146 --> 00:39:19,315
I wasn't into politics at the time,

695
00:39:19,398 --> 00:39:21,233
but we were in a situation

696
00:39:21,317 --> 00:39:24,487
where our country
was starting to make a comeback.

697
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:26,155
It is time for us to realize

698
00:39:26,238 --> 00:39:31,410
that we are too great a nation
to limit ourselves to small dreams.

699
00:39:31,494 --> 00:39:35,664
Those who say that we're in a time
when there are no heroes…

700
00:39:37,249 --> 00:39:39,126
…they just don't know where to look.

701
00:39:39,210 --> 00:39:42,755
And the fans were so, like, "USA!"
All that "USA" and stuff.

702
00:39:42,838 --> 00:39:44,382
Of course he comes out with a flag.

703
00:39:46,842 --> 00:39:49,303
You know, it was just so pro-America

704
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:52,807
that he couldn't even
make a mistake, honestly.

705
00:39:59,438 --> 00:40:00,689
So it was all timing

706
00:40:00,773 --> 00:40:04,193
and being there with the sun,
moon, the stars, everything aligned,

707
00:40:04,276 --> 00:40:06,320
and doing everything at the right moment.

708
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:07,488
The American reality,

709
00:40:07,571 --> 00:40:09,949
I'll tell you what it's about.
It's believing in yourself.

710
00:40:10,032 --> 00:40:12,701
